# 💰 Finance Dashboard Backend API

A scalable backend system for managing financial records with **role-based access control**, **secure authentication**, and **dashboard analytics**.

---

## 🚀 Project Overview

This project is built as a backend for a finance dashboard where users can:

* Track income and expenses
* View financial summaries and trends
* Access features based on their role

The system is designed with a clean architecture and focuses on **data correctness, access control, and maintainability**.

---

## 🧠 Core Features

### 🔐 Authentication & Security

* JWT-based authentication
* Password hashing using bcrypt
* Protected routes using middleware
* Account activation/deactivation support

---

### 👥 Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)

| Role    | Permissions                              |
| ------- | ---------------------------------------- |
| Viewer  | View dashboard data                      |
| Analyst | View records + analytics                 |
| Admin   | Full access (records + users management) |

✔ Implemented using middleware (`protect`, `restrictTo`)

---

### 🧾 Financial Records Management

Each record includes:

* Amount
* Type (`income` / `expense`)
* Category
* Date
* Notes
* CreatedBy (user reference)

#### Features:

* Create records (Admin only)
* Read records (role-based)
* Update records
* Soft delete (`isDeleted`)
* Filtering:

  * type
  * category
  * date range
* Pagination support

---

### 📊 Dashboard & Analytics

Efficient aggregation queries implemented using MongoDB:

* Total income
* Total expenses
* Net balance
* Category-wise breakdown
* Monthly trends
* Weekly trends
* Recent activity

✔ Dashboard is **user-specific** (non-admin users only see their own data)

---

### 🛡️ Validation & Error Handling

* Input validation using `express-validator`
* Custom error class (`AppError`)
* Centralized error handling middleware
* Consistent API response format

---

## 🏗️ Tech Stack

* **Node.js**
* **Express.js (v4)** ⚠️ (used for stability)
* **MongoDB + Mongoose**
* **JWT** (Authentication)
* **bcryptjs** (Password hashing)

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```id="l4t9tm"
src/
├── config/        # DB connection
├── controllers/   # Request handlers
├── services/      # Business logic (dashboard)
├── models/        # Mongoose schemas
├── routes/        # API routes
├── middleware/    # Auth & RBAC
├── utils/         # Error handling
```

---

## 🔑 Authentication Flow

1. User registers or logs in
2. Server returns JWT token
3. Client sends token in header:

```id="r8q53u"
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

4. Middleware verifies token and attaches user to request

---

## 📡 API Endpoints

### 🔐 Auth

| Method | Endpoint           | Description      |
| ------ | ------------------ | ---------------- |
| POST   | /api/auth/register | Register user    |
| POST   | /api/auth/login    | Login user       |
| GET    | /api/auth/me       | Get current user |

---

### 🧾 Records

| Method | Endpoint                  | Description                             |
| ------ | ------------------------- | --------------------------------------- |
| POST   | /api/records              | Create record (Admin only)              |
| GET    | /api/records              | Get records (with filters & pagination) |
| GET    | /api/records/:id          | Get single record                       |
| PATCH  | /api/records/:id          | Update record                           |
| DELETE | /api/records/:id          | Soft delete record                      |
| GET    | /api/records/meta/options | Get categories & types                  |

---

### 📊 Dashboard

| Method | Endpoint                      | Description              |
| ------ | ----------------------------- | ------------------------ |
| GET    | /api/dashboard/summary        | Income, expense, balance |
| GET    | /api/dashboard/categories     | Category breakdown       |
| GET    | /api/dashboard/trends/monthly | Monthly trends           |
| GET    | /api/dashboard/trends/weekly  | Weekly trends            |
| GET    | /api/dashboard/activity       | Recent activity          |

---

### 👥 Users (Admin Only)

| Method | Endpoint              | Description         |
| ------ | --------------------- | ------------------- |
| GET    | /api/users            | Get all users       |
| GET    | /api/users/:id        | Get user            |
| PATCH  | /api/users/:id/role   | Update role         |
| PATCH  | /api/users/:id/status | Activate/deactivate |
| DELETE | /api/users/:id        | Delete user         |

---

## ⚙️ Setup Instructions

### 1️⃣ Clone repository

```id="k7dlp7"
git clone <your-repo-link>
cd finance-dashboard
```

---

### 2️⃣ Install dependencies

```id="p1r1pu"
npm install
```

---

### 3️⃣ Create `.env` file

```id="j79x8m"
PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_connection
JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key
JWT_EXPIRES_IN=7d
NODE_ENV=development
```

---

### 4️⃣ Run server

```id="08tzdy"
npm run dev
```

---

## 🧪 Testing Guide

Use Postman or Thunder Client.

### 🔑 Add token in headers:

```id="31z8r7"
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

---

## 🧠 Design Decisions

* Used **service layer** for dashboard logic separation
* Implemented **soft delete** to preserve data history
* Enforced **RBAC at middleware level**
* Used **MongoDB aggregation pipelines** for performance
* Ensured **user-specific data isolation**

---

## ⚠️ Challenges & Fixes

* Fixed middleware issues caused by Express v5 → downgraded to v4
* Resolved `next is not a function` error caused by Mongoose pre-save hook
* Simplified validation flow for consistency

---

